Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @water{300%ml} and @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @Green Beans{80%g}, then cut into thirds.

Trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} and beans. Use a #spoon to mash the burgers into a mince-like texture as it cooks.

Cook until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Add the pak choi and garlic to the mince. Stir fry for ~{1%min}.

Stir in the @Gochujang Paste{50%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to the boil.

Once boiling, reduce the heat and simmer until the pork is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{3-4%mins}. Stir occasionally.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat. Stir in the @BBQ Sauce{48%g}.

Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper if needed.

Share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the gochujang BBQ plant-based mince.

Sprinkle over the @Crispy Onions{1%sachet} to finish. Enjoy!